                <!-- What is ODM -->
                <section id="what-is-odm" class="mb-16">
                    <div class="bg-brandOrange rounded-2xl p-8 text-white mb-8">
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black uppercase italic mb-4">2. What is ODM for Chargers? (Original Design Manufacturer)</h2>
                        <p class="text-white/80">ODM (Original Design Manufacturing) means the factory provides ready-made designs—you choose from their catalog and customize with your branding. Private labeling, fast time-to-market, low tooling cost.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">The ODM model leverages the factory's existing product portfolio. Think of it as "private label" manufacturing. The factory has already invested in tooling, R&D, and product development. You select from their catalog, add your branding, and they produce. This is similar to how retailers like Amazon Basics or Costco's Kirkland products work.</p>
                    
                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">ODM factories typically maintain 50-200+ active product designs across various categories. These are proven designs with established supply chains, reducing production risks. Your customization focuses on <strong>branding</strong> (logo, colors, packaging) and <strong>surface treatments</strong> (matte black, metallic finish) rather than engineering.</p>
                    
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-slate-900 uppercase italic mb-6">When ODM Makes Sense</h3>
                    
                    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
                        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-6">
                            <h4 class="font-black text-green-700 uppercase mb-3"><svg class="icon-check mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 448 512">
    <path d="M434.8 70.1c14.3 10.4 17.5 30.4 7.1 44.7l-256 352c-5.5 7.6-14 12.3-23.4 13.1s-18.5-2.7-25.1-9.3l-128-128c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l101.5 101.5 234-321.7c10.4-14.3 30.4-17.5 44.7-7.1z" fill="currentColor"/>
  </svg>Choose ODM If:</h4>
                            <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
                                <li>—You're new to product development</li>
                                <li>—You want faster time-to-market (3-6 weeks)</li>
                                <li>—You prefer customizing existing designs</li>
                                <li>—Working with a limited startup budget</li>
                                <li>—Testing a new market or product category</li>
                                <li>—Needing lower MOQs (200-500 units)</li>
                                <li>—Prioritizing speed over uniqueness</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
                            <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-3">ODM Process Flow:</h4>
                            <ol class="space-y-3 text-slate-600 text-sm">
                                <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="font-bold text-brandOrange">1.</span> Browse factory's product catalog</li>
                                <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="font-bold text-brandOrange">2.</span> Select base design(s) for your brand</li>
                                <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="font-bold text-brandOrange">3.</span> Customize logo placement and artwork</li>
                                <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="font-bold text-brandOrange">4.</span> Choose colors and surface finishes</li>
                                <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="font-bold text-brandOrange">5.</span> Design custom packaging</li>
                                <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="font-bold text-brandOrange">6.</span> Sample approval (1-2 weeks)</li>
                                <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="font-bold text-brandOrange">7.</span> Production and shipment</li>
                            </ol>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-6">
                        <h4 class="font-black text-blue-700 uppercase mb-3"><svg class="icon-lightbulb mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 384 512">
    <path d="M292.9 384c7.3-22.3 21.9-42.5 38.4-59.9 32.7-34.4 52.7-80.9 52.7-132.1 0-106-86-192-192-192S0 86 0 192c0 51.2 20 97.7 52.7 132.1 16.5 17.4 31.2 37.6 38.4 59.9l201.7 0zM288 432l-192 0 0 16c0 44.2 35.8 80 80 80l32 0c44.2 0 80-35.8 80-80l0-16zM184 112c-39.8 0-72 32.2-72 72 0 13.3-10.7 24-24 24s-24-10.7-24-24c0-66.3 53.7-120 120-120 13.3 0 24 10.7 24 24s-10.7 24-24 24z" fill="currentColor"/>
  </svg>Pro Tip</h4>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">ODM doesn't mean your product looks identical to competitors. Strategic customization——exclusive colors, premium packaging, added accessories, bundle deals——creates perceived value. Our <a href="/service" class="text-brandBlue underline">ODM customization options</a> include over 15 color variants and custom box designs. <a href="https://www.fluxpanda.com/blog/odm-vs-oem" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue underline">Compare ODM vs private label manufacturing</a></p>
                    </div>
                    
